race.description: Rq Supports Safety In Racing Handicap (Bm90)
race.comment: BULLION BOY (3) has placed four of five around this circuit and has been racing very consistently this time in work. Sticks at the mile now and should be right there when the judge calls a halt. VICTORY WIN (6) strips fitter second-up from the break and gets the services of Maloney in the irons. Top-three credentials. YET HE MOVES (4) has a handy record here with three wins and two placings from eight spins. Keep safe from the Waller yard. EXTRAORDINAIRE (9) rounds out the selections down in the weights. KEITEL (7) showed good improvement second up when winning at the Sunshine Coast. Early signs since heading to QLD most encouraging.
